# Styling Guide

This project uses Tailwind CSS and a CSS-first theme defined in [global.css](mdc:src/styles/global.css).

## Key Styling Principles

1. Prefer Tailwind utility classes for most component styling.
2. Define and reuse design tokens in the `@theme` block.
3. Keep global and shared CSS in `src/styles/` using `@layer` directives.
4. Add component-level CSS only when utilities cannot express the style cleanly.

## Configuration

- Theme tokens are defined in [global.css](mdc:src/styles/global.css) via `@theme`.
- Tailwind is integrated with the `@tailwindcss/vite` plugin in [astro.config.mjs](mdc:astro.config.mjs).
- Dark mode behavior is driven by the `data-color-mode` attribute and related variants.

## Best Practices

1. Use `@layer base` for resets and element defaults.
2. Use `@layer components` for reusable style patterns that appear across files.
3. Use `@layer utilities` for targeted custom utilities.
4. Prefer responsive and state variants (`md:`, `hover:`, `focus:`, dark variants) over ad hoc CSS.
5. Use token-backed semantic utilities (for example `text-primary`, `bg-accent`) when available.

